spanGrp.span: I am Unyangi, the daughter of Baheeba
Mimi ni unyangi binti wa Baheba
In the old days when I was growing up
I hear that in the old days the Asimjeeg they were
In the old days they were
hosh ba someegan qay gayinyay geng'adaj ar ng'arang'
There in Someega I hear in the old days that were even farming peanuts
Kule Somega nasikia zamani huwa wanalima hata karanga
gil seen aa dumd nyiis gesarman aa qana qo qamn ar hosh ba somegan ed qay mid asimjeeg
Whatever, for example the dances, often they were doing them a lot, even there in Someega, where the Asimjeeg were
Chochote mfano ngoma huwa wacheza sana hata sasa kule somega walikokuwa waasimjega
ed qay sarmaniis asimjeeg aa qo qamn
The place where they were dancing until now
Mahali walikokuwa wanachezea ngoma mpaka sasa
The boys who would go to the bush from time to time
Vijana wanaoenda mara kwa mara porini
qareed qay sing'atiis ng'arang gadgwanda ng'arang qaremang nyees gaway aa qok ng'arang'
The buildings where they farmed peanuts in the old days, they are still around even today, peanuts, the youth they go to eat peanuts
Nyumba wanaolima karanga zamani bado zipo mpaka leo karanga vijana wanaenda na kula karanga
asees ha isiheetu istoriyajeg qay siyiinyay aa suhu
When we grew up, the stories we heard were these
Sisi tulipokua historia tulizozisikia ni hizi
Later the Asimjeeg were finished by a snake
They were eaten by a snake until
fiis ng'ay lagan baa asimjeegan iidu amarj qwaloot aa gaway mang'ol
A few Asimjeeg remained, and others left to go until Mang'ola
'Wachache waasimjeega waliosalia wengine waliondoka mpaka mang''ola'
gwand ga mid mang'olajeega aa qamn galagan qamn asees sind law
There are those who stayed in Mang'ola, and those others who remained, we are here in Law
'Kuna walioko Mang''ola sasa waliobaki wengine ni sisi tupo Musoma'
asees ha qay aa gehetu gehetu
In the old days when we grew up, we grew up
In a world that isn't here anymore, even the machines
Katika dunia isiyokuwepo hata na mashine
nyeea qwaloot an iim gaway jeed ng'adood
Our parents often they left to go to the field
Me, I will be the person with the child
The person to look after the children
The corn in the old days they hit it
gibar boog aa giding'd laqaneed ng'asheen
They hit it and ground it with a stone
Unapiga mahindi na kusaga kwenye jiwe
ging'al booga gwand laqaneed sing'aliid boog
You grind corn, there is a stone which is often used to grind corn
Unasaga mahindi kuna jiwe huwa linatumika kusaga mahindi
And to repeat grinding the flour
Na ya marudio ya kusagia unga
ging'ash am qoyid gilot aa gun bidi seng'
You grind, and if you finish you go to cut vegetables
guw bid seng aa ginuny aa giwooschi
You go to cut vegetables, you come to cook
giqon qwayiid fug ga hes aa gol ahiid gil sen ar beeg giramja
The older people will return and you will have already finished everything, you've even fetched water
Watarudi watu wakubwa na utakuwa umemaliza kila kitu hata maji umechota
guwoscheeja qwayiid buneed aa gwagich gijagobur aparood
You have cooked, people have arrived, they are eating, they will be tired from farming
Umepika watu wakifika wanakula watakuwa wamechoka kwa kulima
bas anin hay qay gidaday aa nihi
Well, me, in the old days what I saw was this
Basi mimi zamani nilichoona ndicho hicho
gehetu hay aa ewu haweg heesi
We grew until we became older
If I look, the time when we were growing up
ar gich un jeed tumd eequs aa gehondaneny ii manung' ehondaneny ar dumd aa miwun
Even to go to the dances it was necessary to go to the youth instruction, if it is still difficult to go to the dances
Hata kwenda ngoma lazima upitie mafunzo ya vijana kama bado kwenda ngoma ni ngumu
gich ehondaneeny giqany qahondaneeny fukaheea haweg ga heesi
To be sent to instruction, you are instructed by the older women
Kupelekwa mafunzoni utafunzwa na wakubwa wasichana wakubwa
imid hud qawoong haw sicha qany
If there is an older girl of your home, she will be there
Kama kuna binti wa kwenu mkubwa atakaye
She will advise you until you are instructed
iiya wu ha hondaneed gehoondaneeny ha
If you are done with the instruction
You can enter into the youth dances
Unaweza kuingia katikati ya ngoma ya vijana
aa ii manung' eehondaneeny ar jeed dumd aa miwun
And if you haven't been given instruction, you can't even enter the dances
Na kama hujapewa mafunzo hata kwenye ngoma hutaingia
I think you are still young
anin qay buneed aa gwahetu geyiinyany fug qay
In the old days when people were growing up, often we heard that people in the old days
Zamani watu wakikua huwa tunasikia watu wa zamani
Often they were wearing animal skins
nyas gokwal dung'weend siid aa gokwal aa gek mushk
Often a person would wear an animal skin, and they would wear shoes made of animal skin
Huwa mtu anavaa ngozi na anavaa na viatu vya ngozi
asees gehetu hay ng'ashees aa manung' eeda
When we greaw up, these things we didn't see
asees gehetu hay aa gehetiis jeed ang'wak
When we grew up, we grew up wearing clothes
Sisi tulipokua tulikua katika hali ya kuvaa nguo
ang'wak sang'sang' ar gek rabajeeg gek mushk madedaha
Many clothes, sandals, animal skin shoes we don't see anymore
Nguo nyingi viatu ya raba viatu vya ngozi hatuzioni tena
And I think they would still be around
ng'asheeg qay ar asees gwach gijetaman gicha eeda
The things of the past, we would like to see them
Mambo ya zamani na sisi tungetamani tuyaone
And because of growing up with other varioous tribes
Na ni kwa sababu ya kukua katika makabila mbalimbali
qamn hay aa mad eyada gitatonyandumeed
And now we don't follow the Datooga ways
mad enal much ar gitatonyandumed batood geguyeewej eemoojig sang'
We don't know even our language, because of mixing with many tribes
Hatujui tena hata lugha yetu kwa sababu ya kuchangamana na makabila mengi
nyaas geyad iit eemoojig aa geyad iit
Often we bring the language of the people, to speak the language
Huwa tunaleta lugha ya watu kwa kuongea lugha ya
Of Datooga, that is, of Asimjeeg
We don't do it like it was
aa iyang'ulay aa gad equs giyeet aa asimjeeg
And if I look, they would still be on their own, the Asimjeeg
Na nikiangalia wangekuwa bado wapo peke yao waasimjeega
If I look, I think things would be good
qamn hay asees iyang'ulay saygwedaany qamaj qang'wan
And now if I look, my age set would be better
Na sasa nikiangalia rika yetu ilikuwepo na uafadhali
saygwedaab qamn aa mad eyiiny iit
The age set today, we don't know each other
gigwarugs siid qamat ng'ashand aa qom gotels gong'awaj
A mother will tell them something, and they can answer hatefully
Mama atamwambia neno na anaweza kumjibu kwa kumtukana
giqwanyarees ajinoochand aa qabar ar niny seen gigaguyadaw gabarjudayeew
The mother will get angry and beat them, and they will prepare to fight each other
Mama naye atakasirika na kumpiga na yeye anajiandaa kupigana
bade ja qoheeahim qamat aa qon
Instead of respecting the mother and father
The age set today, if I look, they don't have any respect anymore
Rika ya leo nikiangalia hawana heshima tena
If I look, my history is like this
